## Icon Generation

You can generate these icons from a single source image using tools like:
- https://realfavicongenerator.net/
- https://www.pwabuilder.com/imageGenerator
- ImageMagick (command line)

### ImageMagick Example

```bash
# From a 1024x1024 source image
convert source.png -resize 72x72 icon-72.png
convert source.png -resize 96x96 icon-96.png
convert source.png -resize 128x128 icon-128.png
convert source.png -resize 144x144 icon-144.png
convert source.png -resize 152x152 icon-152.png
convert source.png -resize 192x192 icon-192.png
convert source.png -resize 384x384 icon-384.png
convert source.png -resize 512x512 icon-512.png
```

### Maskable Icons

For maskable icons, ensure there's a safe zone of at least 40% around your icon content.

### Design Guidelines

- Use PNG format with transparency
- Ensure icons work on both light and dark backgrounds
- Follow platform-specific guidelines:
  - iOS: Rounded corners applied automatically
  - Android: Adaptive icons with safe zones
  - Windows: Solid background color

